<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-07-07T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-07-07T15:00:00-05:00" n="97" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d97">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">839.00/2214a suppl.: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Chargé des Affaires in the Dominican
                                    Republic</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Brewer</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-07-07T16:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">July 7,
                                            1920—4 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                            <p>21. Pending decision regarding other matters now under consideration
                                in the Department, you will suggest to Admiral Snowden the
                                desirability of postponing for the present appointment of commission
                                referred to in Department’s instruction, Number 350, dated June 3,
                                1920.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Davis</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>